<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,746,1603]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
TYPE LOCALITY. Originally “in deserti australioris collibus ardentissimis” (
<bibRefCitation author="Pallas, P. S." box="[1068,1213,815,840]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refId="ref61618" refString="Pallas, P. S. (1771) Reise durch verschiedene Provinzen des Russisches Reichs. Kaiserlichen Akademie der Wissenschaften, St. Petersburg, 504 pp." type="book" year="1771">Pallas 1771</bibRefCitation>
); restricted to the “Inderskija Gory, Gebiet des unteren Uralflusses” [region of lower Ural River, W 
<collectingCountry box="[1121,1255,850,875]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
] by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mertens, R. &amp; Muller, L." pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 62" refId="ref58855" refString="Mertens, R. &amp; Muller, L. (1928) Liste der Amphibien und Reptilien Europas. Abhandlungen der Senckenbergischen Naturfoschenden Gesellschaft, 41, 1 - 62." type="journal article" year="1928">Mertens &amp; Müller (1928)</bibRefCitation>
. This restriction was not accompanied by a 
<typeStatus box="[828,931,885,910]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">lectotype</typeStatus>
or 
<typeStatus box="[973,1062,886,910]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">neotype</typeStatus>
designation and is therefore not valid as such (
<bibRefCitation author="Uetz, P." box="[310,433,919,944]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refId="ref67280" refString="Uetz, P. (2013) The Reptile database. Available from: http: // www. reptile-database. org / (accessed 8 July 2014)" type="url" year="2013">Uetz 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,746,1603]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
DISTRIBUTION. SE part of European 
<collectingCountry box="[569,646,954,979]" name="Russia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Russia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[659,793,954,979]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[805,963,954,979]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[977,1106,954,979]" name="Uzbekistan" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Uzbekistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1118,1250,955,979]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1263,1378,954,979]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
, NW 
<collectingCountry box="[151,218,989,1014]" name="China" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[272,385,989,1014]" name="Mongolia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,746,1603]" box="[151,1264,1023,1048]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
DISTRIBUTION IN 
<collectingCountry box="[349,405,1024,1047]" name="Iran" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">IRAN</collectingCountry>
. 
<figureCitation box="[420,502,1023,1048]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–19. 14" captionStartId="74.[151,264,1557,1580]" captionTargetBox="[171,1416,213,1516]" captionTargetId="figure-63@74.[151,1436,193,1536]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURES 14–19. 14. Phrynocephalus helioscopus. 15. Phrynocephalus maculatus. 16. Phrynocephalus mystaceus. 17. Phrynocephalus ornatus. Blue square denotes the type locality for P. o. vindumi. 18. Phrynocephalus persicus. 19. Phrynocephalus scutellatus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4929713" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4929713/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
. Occurs only by the borders with Turkmenistan by the Caspian Sea.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,746,1603]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">HABITAT. Clay and stony deserts, sometimes sandy areas with high admixture of pebbles, usually in areas of sparse vegetation.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,746,1603]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
REMARKS. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Filippi" authorityYear="1863" box="[279,563,1127,1152]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Phrynocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis box="[279,563,1127,1152]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Phrynocephalus persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was separated from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1771" box="[804,970,1127,1152]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Phrynocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="helioscopus">
<emphasis box="[804,970,1127,1152]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">P. helioscopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of the analysis of allozyme variation (
<bibRefCitation author="Mezhzherin, S. V. &amp; Golubev, M. L." box="[267,607,1162,1187]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="72 - 74" refId="ref59156" refString="Mezhzherin, S. V. &amp; Golubev, M. L. (1989) The genetic divergence of Phrynocephalus Kaup (Reptilia, Agamidae) of the USSR fauna [in Russian]. Reports of Ukraine SSR Academy of Sciences. Series B Geology, Chemistry and Biological Sciences, 12, 72 - 74." type="journal article" year="1989">Mezhzherin &amp; Golubev 1989</bibRefCitation>
). There is an immense chaos regarding the form 
<taxonomicName authority="Mehely" authorityName="Mehely" box="[1170,1358,1162,1187]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Phrynocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="horvathi">
<emphasis box="[1170,1265,1162,1187]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">horvathi</emphasis>
Méhely
</taxonomicName>
which was originally described as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1771" box="[633,796,1197,1222]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Phrynocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="helioscopus">
<emphasis box="[633,796,1197,1222]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">P. helioscopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the foothills of 
<collectingRegion box="[1033,1108,1197,1222]" country="Armenia" name="Ararat" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Ararat</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1118,1216,1197,1222]" name="Armenia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Armenia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mehely, L." box="[1230,1381,1197,1222]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="81 - 87" refId="ref58344" refString="Mehely, L. (1894) Beitrage zur Herpetologie Transkaukasiens und Armeniens. Zoologischer Anzeiger, 17, 81 - 87." type="journal article" year="1894">Méhely 1894</bibRefCitation>
) and which is endemic to E 
<collectingCountry box="[419,519,1231,1256]" name="Turkey" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
, S 
<collectingCountry box="[557,658,1231,1256]" name="Armenia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Armenia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[672,795,1231,1256]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
and NW 
<collectingCountry box="[910,959,1232,1255]" name="Iran" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Iran</collectingCountry>
. In 
<collectingCountry box="[1004,1049,1232,1255]" name="Iran" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Iran</collectingCountry>
it is restricted to the vicinity and north of the Lake Urmia (
<bibRefCitation author="Melnikov, D. A. &amp; Ananjeva, N. B. &amp; Agasyan, A. L. &amp; Rajabizadeh, M." box="[439,681,1266,1291]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="286 - 297" refId="ref58367" refString="Melnikov, D. A., Ananjeva, N. B., Agasyan, A. L. &amp; Rajabizadeh, M. (2008) Historical background and taxonomic status of the Persian toad head agama, Phrynocephalus persicus de Filippi, 1863 and Horvath's sun watcher toad head agama Phrynocephalus helioscopus horvathi Mehely, 1894. In: Ananjeva, N. B., Danilov, I. G., Dunayev, E. A., Ishchenko, V. G., Lada, G. A., Litvinchuk, S. N., Orlova, V. F., Smirina, E. M., Tuniyev, B. S. &amp; Khalikov, R. G. (Eds.), The problems of herpetology. Proceedings of the 3 th Meeting of the Nikolsky Herpetological Society 9 - 13 October 2006, Putschino, pp. 286 - 297." type="book chapter" year="2008">
Melnikov 
<emphasis box="[556,613,1266,1291]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
). Some authors treat this form as it was described—a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1771" box="[151,320,1301,1326]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Phrynocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="helioscopus">
<emphasis box="[151,320,1301,1326]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">P. helioscopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rastegar-Pouyani, N. &amp; Kami, H. G. &amp; Rajabzadeh, M. &amp; Shafiei, S. &amp; Anderson, S. C." box="[341,690,1301,1326]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="43 - 66" refId="ref63314" refString="Rastegar-Pouyani, N., Kami, H. G., Rajabzadeh, M., Shafiei, S. &amp; Anderson, S. C. (2008) Annotated checklist of Amphibians and Reptiles of Iran. Iranian Journal of Animal Biosystematics, 4, 43 - 66." type="journal article" year="2008">
Rastegar-Pouyani 
<emphasis box="[555,618,1301,1326]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tosunoglu, M. &amp; Gul, C. &amp; Topyildiz, H. &amp; Uysal, I." box="[708,976,1301,1326]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="247 - 252" refId="ref67094" refString="Tosunoglu, M., Gul, C., Topyildiz, H. &amp; Uysal, I. (2011) Notes on Distribution, Ecology, and Morphological Characters of Phrynocephalus helioscopus horvathi Mehely, 1894 from Northeast Anatolia. Russian Journal of Herpetology, 18, 247 - 252." type="journal article" year="2011">
Tosunoğlu 
<emphasis box="[840,903,1301,1326]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
), some as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Filippi" authorityYear="1863" box="[1305,1436,1302,1325]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Phrynocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis box="[1305,1436,1302,1325]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">P. persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Barabanov, A. V. &amp; Ananjeva, N. B." box="[158,497,1335,1360]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 56" refId="ref46583" refString="Barabanov, A. V. &amp; Ananjeva, N. B. (2007) Catalogue of the available scientific species-group names for lizards of the genus Phrynocephalus Kaup, 1825 (Reptilia, Sauria, Agamidae). Zootaxa, 1399, 1 - 56." type="journal article" year="2007">Barabanov &amp; Ananjeva 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Arakelyan, M. &amp; Danielyan, F. &amp; Corti, C. &amp; Sindaco, R. &amp; Leviton, A. E." box="[511,764,1335,1360]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refId="ref45580" refString="Arakelyan, M., Danielyan, F., Corti, C., Sindaco, R. &amp; Leviton, A. E. (2011) Herpetofauna of Armenia and Nagorno-Karabakh. Society for the Study of Amphibians and Reptiles, Oxford, Ohio, 149 pp." type="book" year="2011">
Arakelyan 
<emphasis box="[637,695,1335,1360]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Solovyeva, E. N. &amp; Poyarkov, N. A. &amp; Dunaev, E. A. &amp; Duysebayeva, T. N. &amp; Bannikova, A. A." box="[777,1031,1335,1360]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="842 - 856" refId="ref65720" refString="Solovyeva, E. N., Poyarkov, N. A., Dunaev, E. A., Duysebayeva, T. N. &amp; Bannikova, A. A. (2011) Molecular Differentiation and Taxonomy of the Sunwatcher Toad Headed Agama Species Complex Phrynocephalus Superspecies helioscopus (Pallas 1771) (Reptilia: Agamidae). Russian Journal of Genetics, 47, 842 - 856. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1134 / s 1022795411070155" type="journal article" year="2011">
Solovyeva 
<emphasis box="[904,963,1335,1360]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Milto, K. D. &amp; Barabanov, A. V." box="[1045,1336,1335,1360]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="155 - 170" refId="ref59215" refString="Milto, K. D. &amp; Barabanov, A. V. (2012) A catalogueof the agamid chamaeleonid types in the collection of the Zoological institute, Russian Academy of Sciences, St. Petersburg. Russian Journal of Herpetology, 19, 155 - 170." type="journal article" year="2012">Milto &amp; Barabanov 2012</bibRefCitation>
) and yet others as a full species (
<bibRefCitation author="Cicek, K. &amp; Ayaz, D. &amp; Tok, C. V. &amp; Tayhan, Y." box="[429,633,1370,1395]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="69 - 73" refId="ref48566" refString="Cicek, K., Ayaz, D., Tok, C. V. &amp; Tayhan, Y. (2011) Data on food composition of Phrynocephalus horvathi Mehely, 1894 (Reptilia: Agamidae) in Mount Ararat (Northeastern Anatolia, Turkey). Ecologia Balkanica, 3, 69 - 73." type="journal article" year="2011">
Çiçek 
<emphasis box="[505,564,1370,1395]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Anderson, S. C." box="[814,1009,1370,1395]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refId="ref45318" refString="Anderson, S. C. (1999) The lizards of Iran. Society for the Study of Amphibians and Reptiles, Oxford, Ohio, 442 pp." type="book" year="1999">Anderson (1999)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1023,1151,1370,1395]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Phrynocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="horvathi">
<emphasis box="[1023,1151,1370,1395]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">P. horvathi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be a younger synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Filippi" authorityYear="1863" box="[293,418,1406,1429]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Phrynocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis box="[293,418,1406,1429]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">P. persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This assumption is in accordance with the results of mtDNA analyses of 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Phrynocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="helioscopuspersicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">P. helioscopuspersicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex by 
<bibRefCitation author="Solovyeva, E. N. &amp; Poyarkov, N. A. &amp; Dunaev, E. A. &amp; Duysebayeva, T. N. &amp; Bannikova, A. A." box="[398,670,1439,1464]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="842 - 856" refId="ref65720" refString="Solovyeva, E. N., Poyarkov, N. A., Dunaev, E. A., Duysebayeva, T. N. &amp; Bannikova, A. A. (2011) Molecular Differentiation and Taxonomy of the Sunwatcher Toad Headed Agama Species Complex Phrynocephalus Superspecies helioscopus (Pallas 1771) (Reptilia: Agamidae). Russian Journal of Genetics, 47, 842 - 856. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1134 / s 1022795411070155" type="journal article" year="2011">
Solovyeva 
<emphasis box="[527,586,1439,1464]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
(2011)
</bibRefCitation>
which proved 
<taxonomicName box="[846,941,1439,1464]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Phrynocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="horvathi">
<emphasis box="[846,941,1439,1464]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">horvathi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be an inner lineage of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Filippi" authorityYear="1863" box="[1248,1375,1440,1464]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Phrynocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis box="[1248,1375,1440,1464]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">P. persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The name 
<taxonomicName box="[222,317,1474,1499]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Phrynocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="horvathi">
<emphasis box="[222,317,1474,1499]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">horvathi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was stabilized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Melnikov, D. &amp; Melnikova, E. &amp; Nazarov, R. &amp; Rajabizadeh, M." box="[540,807,1474,1499]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="34 - 46" refId="ref58533" refString="Melnikov, D., Melnikova, E., Nazarov, R. &amp; Rajabizadeh, M. (2013) Taxonomic revision of Phrynocephalus persicus de Filippi, 1863 complex with description of a new species from Zagros, southern Iran. Modern Herpetology, 2013, 34 - 46." type="journal article" year="2013">
Melnikov 
<emphasis box="[659,719,1474,1499]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
(2013)
</bibRefCitation>
, who designated 
<typeStatus box="[1012,1101,1475,1499]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">neotype</typeStatus>
(see remarks by 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Filippi" authorityYear="1863" box="[1308,1436,1475,1498]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Phrynocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis box="[1308,1436,1475,1498]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">P. persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
below).
</paragraph>
